This is a modal window. Beginning of dialog window. Escape will cancel and close the window. End of dialog window. From Tony Osauzo, Benin Ahead of next Saturday Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) primary to elect its National Assembly candidates across the country, a front line contender for the Edo Central Senatorial seat, Arch. Dr Mike Onolememe, has solicited for delegates votes, promising that his mission is to transform Esan Land from a largely rural place to an urban setting if voted to win the party ticket. Onolememe, a former Minister of Works, made the plea to individual delegates via a voice note he sent to all delegates of the Senatorial District. “I am personally soliciting for your votes in the upcoming primary that will take place, Saturday May 21, 2022”, he said, adding that so much is at stake for the senatorial district. He, therefore, stressed that the delegates must get it right for Esan people. “I am banking on you to win the primary election. There is so much at stake. And we must get right it for Esan people. “Engage and talk to other delegates you know to vote for me,” he said. Onolememe believes that he can win the primary election with votes from the delegates and go on to win the general election. “Please it is an important election that has the potential to transform Esan Land from rural enclave to urban area with enhanced standards of living. “Since an election can be won by a single vote, your vote matters, I assure you, you will not regret supporting me and your vote will be a step forward to making Esan Land a better place,” he added.